  \"symbol\": \"ServerConfig.PeerDialTimeout\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"kubernetes/kubernetes\",\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/factory/etcd3.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"newETCD3Client\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\",\n      \"path\": \"client/v3/client.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"New\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\",\n      \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/server.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"NewServer\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"etcd-io/etcd\",\n      \"path\": \"server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Transport.Start\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"DialTimeout configuration is distributed across the Kubernetes apiserver and etcd codebase. In Kubernetes, the staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/factory/etcd3.go defines a constant dialTimeout of 20 seconds (line 69) that is used to configure the etcd client connection timeout. This timeout accommodates TLS connection establishment on loaded systems. The preflight/checks.go file uses net.DialTimeout for quick connectivity verification (line 39, 1 second timeout). In etcd client (v3), the Config struct (client/v3/config.go, line 35) defines the DialTimeout field that specifies timeout for establishing connections. This configuration is used throughout the client: in client.go (New function), maintenance.go (line 89 checks if DialTimeout > 0), and lease.go. The client/v3/doc.go file provides usage examples showing DialTimeout set to 2-5 seconds. On the server side, etcd defines multiple timeout mechanisms: server/config/config.go implements PeerDialTimeout() method (lines 321-323) that calculates peer connection timeout as 1 second plus election timeout. The server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go defines the Transport.DialTimeout field (line 100) used by the raft protocol transport. The etcd server configuration in server/etcdmain/config.go includes ProxyDialTimeoutMs for proxy settings (line 218, default 1000ms), used in etcd.go and grpc_proxy.go where DialTimeout is set to 5 seconds for proxy client connections (lines 338, 356).\"\n}\n",
